<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toll Rises in North China Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Forty-seven people have died
and over 2,000 people have suffered injuries, including 250 people
with serious injuries, in the earthquake which struck today in
Shangyi and Zhangbei counties in Zhangjiakou Prefecture, north
China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The quake measuring 6.2 on the Richter Scale hit the area,
located some 220 kilometers northwest of Beijing, the Chinese
capital, at 11:50 a.m. (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
The tremors were felt by people living over a large area,
including Baotou and Hohhot in the west, Qinghuangdao and Tianjin
to the east, and Shijiazhuang and Taiyuan to the south.
</P>
<P>
Three aftershocks measuring measuring 4.6, 4.5 and 4.2 on the
Richter Scale were recorded after 18:00 p.m. (Beijing Time),
according to the latest report from the State Seismological Bureau
(SSB).
</P>
<P>
The SSB reports that over 70,000 houses in 13 townships
covering some 1,000 sq km, have either collapsed or sustained
heavy damage, with more than 60,000 structures located in Zhangbei
County, also the county in which 47 people died.
</P>
<P>
The SSB has ruled out the possibility aftershocks measuring
above 6.2 on the Richter Scale in the area of the epicenter, and
predicts ensuing aftershocks will measure less that 5.0 on the
Richter Scale.
</P>
<P>
The report indicates that a provincial Party and government
work team, led by Xu Yongyao, deputy secretary of the Provincial
Party Committee, arrived at the affected area this evening to
direct relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has also allocated relief funds
totalling 500,000 yuan, and medical teams and various relief
supplies have been sent to the area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another team led by officers of the provincial
military command also rushed to the affected area to direct rescue
work by soldiers of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
The Party Central Committee and the State Council are highly
concerned about the well-being of quake victims. with President
and Party General Secretary Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng
calling on provincial leaders in Hebei to assess damage and
exhibit great concern for victims.
</P>
<P>
The SSB has also dispatched a team of 50 experts from central
and local seismological departments, as well as seismological
measuring and monitoring equipment.
</P>
<P>
The SSB has issued a directive for provincial seismological
bureaus in Hebei and Shanxi provinces, the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region and subordinate seismological units to
closely monitor the situation.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the SSB has initiated operations of Beijing Area
Seismological Work Procedures for Emergency Periods in order to
monitor the situation in the area surrounding the capital city,
according to the report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
