<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, January 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Four Palestinian youths were wounded in a severe
clash with Israeli soldiers in the West Bank city of Hebron
Saturday, the Jerusalem Media and Communication Center (JMCC) said.
</P>
<P>
The clash between some 100 Palestinian youths and Israeli
soldiers occurred at an Israeli checkpoint near the Shuhada
Street, which was closed to traffic long time ago following the
clashes between the Palestinians and Jewish settlers in the city.
(Israel-Clash-Hebron)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Takako Doi, leader of Japan's Social Democratic Party
(SDP), was reelected unopposed Saturday for another two-year term.
</P>
<P>
After the reelection, Doi said her party would continue an
alliance with the ruling Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) for the
time being. (Japan-Doi-Reelection)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A Palestinian official Saturday described the talks
held by Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat and
U.S. coordinator of the Mideast peace process Dennis Ross as
"serious," but short of "final results."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Cairo-based Voice of Arabs Radio,
Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO) representative to
Washington Hassan Abdurrahman said Arafat-Ross talks centered on
commitments of the transitional period and arrangements for the
upcoming summit meetings in Washington between the U.S.,
Palestinian and Israeli leaders. (Egypt-Ross-PLO) 
</P>
</TEXT>
