<HEADLINE> Russia, Chechnya Hold Talks on Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 10 (Xinhua) -- A Russian governmental
delegation and the Chechen government held a two-hour talk in
Grozny Saturday on how to restore the economy of the breakaway
republic, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by Deputy Prime Minister Ramazan
Abdulatipov, arrived in Grozny on Saturday morning. "We come to
Chechnya to start a normal, creative work," he said.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the status of Grozny's Severny airport
which Chechens held must be international.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is also expected to meet with the newly-formed
Chechen cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Russia had sent to Chechnya a federal program which earmarks 16
trillion unredenominated rubles (2.6 trillion U.S. dollars) plus 1
billion U.S. dollars for revitalizing the Chechen economy, the
report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
