<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Arrives in Algiers for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen arrived here Saturday afternoon for a
three-day official visit to Algeria.
</P>
<P>
On his arrival at Algiers International Airport, Qian told
reporters that he is satisfied with the friendship between the
peoples of China and Algeria and bilateral cooperation has
achieved good results.
</P>
<P>
Qian added that China and Algeria have supported each other in
international affairs and they have also positively contributed to
protecting the sovereignty and people's rights in the developing
countries, as well as to establishing and promoting regional and
world peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Qian is going to have talks with his
Algerian counterpart Ahmed Attaf, as well as other Algerian top
officials, on ways of promoting bilateral cooperation and a number
of regional and international issues of mutual concern. 
</P>
