<HEADLINE> Japan's Defense Agency Chief Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 10 (xinhua) -- Fumio Kyuma, head of Japan's
defense agency, arrived here Saturday for a short official visit
to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
This marks the first visit by a head of the Japanese Defense
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Defense Minister Pham Van Tra and his Japanese guest
Fumio Kyuma held talks on "issues of common concern",
Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
However, the report did not give the results of the talks.
</P>
<P>
Kyuma also met Vietnamese Prime Minister Phan Van Khai who
described Kyuma's visit as "a contribution to the strengthening of
the friendly relations, cooperation and mutual understanding
between the army and people of the two countries for the common
goal of regional security and stability maintenance."
</P>
<P>
VNA said Khai "spoke highly of the friendly and cooperative
ties between Vietnam and Japan, which he said are very helpful to
the socio-economic construction and development cause in Vietnam
over the past period."
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese prime minister expressed his wish that "these
cooperative relations would be constantly developed, especially in
economy, investment for development, commerce, science and
technology."
</P>
<P>
Kyuma said he hoped that the cooperative relations between the
two countries would be further developed. 
</P>
