<HEADLINE> Montreal Hit Hard by Ice Storm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- People in Canada's second
largest city of Montreal have been told to reduce use of water and
power as downtown Montreal was thrown into darkness and cold by
ravaging ice storms.
</P>
<P>
Quebec Premier Lucien Bouchard has asked Canadian Prime
Minister Jean Chretien for 3,000 more troops to help clean up the
mess caused by a record five days of freezing rain, said reports
today.
</P>
<P>
The premier also asked the United States for beds and
generators.
</P>
<P>
More than 3 million people remained without power in parts of
Quebec, Ontario and the Maritime provinces by late Friday. 
</P>
