<HEADLINE> Ethiopian PM Elected Secretary of EPRDF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi today was elected Secretary of the ruling Ethiopian
People's Revolutionary Democratic Front (EPRDF) at its third
regular conference.
</P>
<P>
The four-day conference of the EPRDF wound up today in Jimma
Town, some 340 kms away from Addis Ababa, after electing
60-member council and 20-member executive committee of the EPRDF.
</P>
<P>
In a resolution issued at the end of the conference, the
participants vowed to contribute their share towards poverty
eradication.
</P>
<P>
The resolution called on farmers and all Ethiopians at large
to continue their participation in the EPRDF's bid to speed-up
the country's economic up-swing. 
