<HEADLINE> Liaoning Beat Lianhang in Chinese Basektball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Liaoning Hunters beat
Lianhang Army Eagles 83-72 in the 14th round of the Hilton Chinese
basketball first division league here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Hunters, runners-up in last season, made an aggressive
start on road with three steals in the opening 90 seconds, leading
the halftime at 43-34.
</P>
<P>
The Eagles stormed back strongly in the second half in the
bunting-flattering, drum-deafening Shijingshan Stadium, tying at
45-45 at 2:15 after they came back.
</P>
<P>
Point guard Liu Tie dunked one free-throw and five baskets in
Eagles' 11-2 run before Hunters pulled away with Li Xiaoyong's
three-point and Wu Naiqun's layup for good.
</P>
<P>
Li chipped in game-high 26 points on his 100-percent
free-throws in six attempts, and Wu added 10 points.
</P>
<P>
Liu Tie scored 24 points, three boards and two steals, and Li
Tao added 10 points and six boards for the Eagles, which recorded
two wins and 12 loses with 16 points.
</P>
<P>
In Jinan, Gong Xiaobin scored a game-high 34 points and grabbed
13 rebounds to lead Shangdong Baoyuan to a 80-68 win over the
visiting Jiangsu Nangang.
</P>
<P>
In the other games, league leader Chinese Army ousted Sichuan
Pandas 92-89, Shenyang Army beat Zhejiang Zhongxin 76-58, Beijing
Shougang defeated Jinan Army 80-62, Guangdong Hongyuan routed
Shanghai Oriental 68-57. 
</P>
</TEXT>
