<HEADLINE> PLA Troops Aid Northern China's Earthquake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of People's
Liberation Army (PLA) troops and People's Armed Police have joined
the rescue efforts in the Zhangjiakou area in northern China,
which was hit by a strong earthquake on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The troops braved sub-zero temperatures Saturday evening to
help people whose houses had been destroyed.
</P>
<P>
People suffering from severe injuries were moved to army
hospitals, while make-shift housing and a large number of tents
were set up in the area.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the quake hit, the PLA Beijing Area Command
Headquarters held an emergency meeting to discuss rescue work and
decided that troops would be sent to the site. In two hours 150
people in five medical teams were sent, followed by 1,000 soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters also sent 5,000 overcoats and 500 tents to
quake victims on Saturday and followed up today with another 1,500
soldiers and more medical workers. Four army helicopters airlifted
30 tons of food to the victims, including bread, steam-bread, and
fast-food.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters is also asking for clothing donations from its
troops, and 1,000 items of clothing have been have been handed out
to villagers.
</P>
<P>
The Armed Police's Hebei Provincial Brigade has sent nearly
1,000 personnel to help maintain order in the area and to help get
the seriously injured to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
They have also sent several medical teams and nearly 500,000
yuan worth of relief materials, 1,000 cotton-padded quilts, 20
tents, and four tons of fast food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
