<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank of China's 1997 Profits Continue Upward Move </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC), the
country's largest foreign exchange bank, had at least 6.03 billion
yuan (about 726 million US dollars) in profits last year, the
largest amount for Chinese financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Of that amount, 2.42 billion yuan came from inside China,
according to a senior bank official.
</P>
<P>
If such unfavorable factors as tax increases, increased amount
of bad loan funds, and drop in interest rates are taken into
consideration, the efficiency of the BOC last year was generally
experiencing an upward trend, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The BOC had 591.2 billion yuan in deposits and 564.4 billion
yuan in outstanding loans at the end of 1997, and year-end foreign
exchange holdings of 35.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The BOC did 139.8 billion US dollars in international trade
business last year. It also issued 7.8 million credit cards, and
did 12 billion yuan in credit card business, 66 percent and 17.6
percent increases over the previous year, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
