<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Belmondo Wins Women's 10km Cross-country Pursuit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Stefania Belmondo of Italy
claimed her first World Cup victory of the season by winning a
10-kilometer cross-country pursuit race in Ramsau, Austria, on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old struggled earlier in the season but she is
regaining form less than a month before the Winter Olympics in
Nagano, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Belmondo, who will be making her fourth Olympic appearance in
Nagano, won the silver medal in 1992 and the bronze medal in 1994
in the same event.
</P>
<P>
She was only 15th in the 5-km classical style race on Friday,
the first leg of the pursuit, beating the second placer Larissa
Lazutina of Russia by 11.8 seconds in Sunday's freestyle portion.
</P>
<P>
Belmondo's combined time of 38 minutes, 4.4 seconds gave her
the 17th victory in a World Cup event in her career.
</P>
<P>
Marit Mikkelsplass of Norway, who was fourth in the 5-km event,
moved to third, 37 seconds behind Belmondo.
</P>
<P>
Bente Martinsen of Norway, who won the 5-km race, finished
seventh to retain her lead in World Cup standings over Lazutina,
531-493.  
</P>
</TEXT>
