<HEADLINE> Hoppe Fails to Make German Olympic Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 11 (Xinhua) -- World's bobsleigh super star
Wolfgang Hoppe failed to qualify for the Winter Olympics in Nagano
when his four-man bob finished only third in the German
championships in Winterberg, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The four-man title went to Olympic champion Harald Czudaj who
beat Dirk Wiese and Hoppe into second and third places
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Wiese took the last remaining driver's place available. He
joined Czudaj and Christoph Langen who had qualified earlier.
</P>
<P>
"There are more important things in life," said 40-year-old
Hoppe who has garnered 33 medals at Olympics, world and European
championships.  
</P>
</TEXT>
