<HEADLINE> US Mediator's Visit Fruitless: Palestinian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Ambassador to
Zimbabwe Ali Halimeh has described the recent visit by the
American Middle East Mediator as having ended without any
positive results.
</P>
<P>
In a statement Saturday, Halimeh said the Israeli Government
and its policies regarding the continued violation of the Oslo
Agreement and refusal to abide by its terms resulted in the
collapse of the talks between Dennis Ross and the Israeli and
Palestinian officials.
</P>
<P>
The decision by Israeli authorities to pursue its activities
of building more settlements in the Palestinian land of the West
Bank, and the continued policies of confiscating Palestinian land
would lead to the collapse of the entire peace process and
encourage more violence in the area, he warned.
</P>
<P>
"We view this decision as a very dangerous move and it may
bring down the American efforts to put the peace process into the
correct road and track," said Halimeh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
