<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe/DRC Friendship Association Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe and Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) Friendship Association was inaugurated
Saturday in Harare to promote social, economic and cultural links
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The move to form the association comes soon after the Zimbabwean
government opened a diplomatic mission in Kinshasa, the capital of
the DRC.
</P>
<P>
Launching the association at the DRC Embassy here, Zimbabwean
Minister of Information, Posts and Telecommunications Chen
Chimutengwende said relations between the DRC and Zimbabwe were
set to grow stronger, especially given the fact that the former
Zaire now led by President Laurent Kabila had become a member of
the Southern African Development Community.
</P>
<P>
Phillip Chiyangwa, who is a Harare businessman, has became
chairman of the association. He is also the head of the native
investments Africa group which has secured a 400 million
Zimbabwean Dollars (23 million U.S. Dollars) facility to export
goods to the DRC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
