<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Providing Disaster Relief For The Tibetan Snowstorm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGQU (Tibet), January 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 110,000 people
in snowstorm-ravaged parts of northern Tibet's Nagqu Prefecture
have received food, clothing and other disaster-relief materials
from various provinces and the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Most victims have received help, and rescue workers have
removed snow accumulation from most roads leading to 110 snow-hit
towns more than 5,000 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, the government has been concerned about
people in snowstorm-hit parts of Tibet, and the PLA has sent
vehicles and soldiers to assist the victims, while military
aircraft have airlifted large quantities of relief materials to
these areas.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has also played an important role by
dispatching eight rescue teams to join the effort. Several dozen
bulldozers and 30 tractors have been working day and night to
re-open mountain roads.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 heavy snowfalls have hit Nagqu since September,
dumping 40 centimeters of snow in many villages and 80 centimeters
on mountainous areas and cutting herdsmen's connections with the
outside world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
