<HEADLINE> Relief Activities For Quake-Hit Area Of Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The government of northern
China's Hebei Province has held three emergency meetings to deal
with the effects of the earthquake that hit Zhangjiakou Prefecture
yesterday and to provide relief for the victims.
</P>
<P>
Governor Ye Liansong has rushed to the site to direct the
rescue work in the damage caused by the earthquake, which measured
6.2 on the Richter Scale. The provincial government has allocated
one million yuan in relief funds and tents, cotton-padded
clothing, and quilts to the area, and 13 medical teams have gone
there.
</P>
<P>
