<HEADLINE> Agricultural Bank Maintaining Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
made 510 million yuan (about 61 million US dollars) in net profits
for 1997, according to early statistics.
</P>
<P>
The amount is roughly the same as for 1996, the bank's
president, He Linxiang, said at a news briefing today, where he
reported healthy growth for last year, with internal reforms going
on smoothly.
</P>
<P>
ABC had more than 1.1 trillion yuan in savings deposits at the
end of 1997, up 21.8 percent from the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
He said that ABC increased financial support for agriculture
last year, with annual amount of agricultural loans rising 32.5
billion yuan, a 19 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
He also said that ABC's loans for the "Vegetable Basket"
program, a national project to ensure vegetable and meat supplies,
were up 16 percent to 22 billion yuan. The agricultural bank's
loans for township-run enterprises were 20.9 billion yuan last
year, up 12 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
This year, ABC will try to improve its efficiency in per capita
terms and reduce the amount of bad loans, He said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
