<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Bank to Help Private Entrepreneurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Commercial
Bank plans to grant loans amounting to 10.6 billion Birr (about
1.54 billion U.S Dollars) during the current Ethiopian fiscal
year ending July 7 to private entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
According to a local press report here, Mulugeta Gebre-Medhin,
Assistant Deputy President of the credit analysis and review
department in the bank, said the bulk of the stated sum will be
disbursed to private businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Mulugeta said the bank, the largest financial institute in
Ethiopia, gave them nearly 8 billion Birr (about 1.16 billion U.S
Dollars) in the previous fiscal year of which 5.712 billion Birr
(0.83 billion U.S Dollars) had been repaid.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Commercial Bank, which has 19 billion Birr (2.77
billion U.S. Dollars) of capital and whose branch offices have
reached 170, covers 90 percent of bank's services in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to Mulugeta, the bank also covers over 80 percent of
loan services to small farmers or peasants in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ethiopian Development Bank has also said it is
ready to extend loans amounting to 775 million Birr (113 million
U.S Dollars) to its clients during the current fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of loans exceeds that of the previous year by 151
million Birr (22 million U.S. Dollars), the bank said. 
</P>
