<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Province Moves to Protect Agricultural Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has promulgated a revised regulation to protect its
agricultural environment.
</P>
<P>
According the Provincial Agricultural Department, with the
industrial and agricultural growth in Liaoning, pollution is
affecting the agricultural environment.
</P>
<P>
Last year, there were 41 pollution cases in Liaoning's farming
production which resulted in losses of 49.55 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
To address the situation, the province recently promulgated the
regulation and handled 32 pollution cases by imposing fines of
13.82 million yuan on polluters.
</P>
<P>
The revised regulation stresses that industrial production
should not damage the agricultural environment, which prohibits
dumping poisonous matters, wastes and wastewater.
</P>
<P>
The regulation also stipulates that agricultural production
should not spoil the farming environment. It encourages the
establishment of non-polluting farming bases to produce green food
and organic food, and to adopt organic pesticides and fertilizers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
