identified during his visit. "Discussions on a follow-up order for
railways equipment have already started," he added.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will export complete plants and equipment and the
engineering components such as pumps and electric motors to Sri
Lanka, according to Aziz.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said that Pakistan's exports to Sri Lanka based on
textiles and rice had "increased substantially" last year.
Addition of new items will broaden the base of Pakistan's exports,
he added.
</P>
<P>
"In addition to exporting complete plants, Pakistan will also
help Sri Lanka start up indigenous processing and manufacturing of
agricultural and engineering goods," he said.  
