<HEADLINE> Maier Wins Super-G Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Hermann Maier clinched his
second World Cup super-G slalom victory within 24 hours in
Schladming, Austria on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Maier, who posted one minute 14.84 seconds, led the Austrian
men in their fourth sweep of the podium places this season with
Andreas Schifferer second in 1:16.03 and Stefan Eberharter third
in 1:16.14.
</P>
<P>
Another Austrian, Rainer Salzgeber, shared fourth place with
Italy's Peter Runggaldier.
</P>
<P>
The super-G got off to an extraordinary start with five of the
first six racers, including former Olympic and world downhill
champion Patrick Ortlieb of Austria, missing gates on the icy
Planai course.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's top three finishers have been the most dominant skiers
this season. The trio hold the leading three spots in the overall
standings with Maier first on 1,019 points.
</P>
<P>
Austrian men have won 13 of the 18 races staged so far this
season. 
</P>
