<HEADLINE> Man Killed In Belfast Club Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 11 (Xinhua) - A man was shot dead by gunmen in
a car at a club in Belfast, capital of Northern Ireland, early on
Sunday, BBC reported.
</P>
<P>
The victim was one of several doormen who were standing outside
the club.
</P>
<P>
A police spokeswoman said the gunmen pulled up outside the club
in a taxi. A man started firing from a seated position in the taxi
over the roof at security staff, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The taxi was later found burnt out in the east of the
city. Police said they have not yet established a motive for the
attack.
</P>
<P>
Since Christmas three people have been shot dead by rival
pro-British and republican guerrilla factions opposed to peace
efforts by British and Irish governments, the report added.
</P>
