<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Strengthen Police Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano said that his country has started to train more police
under the help of international community.
</P>
<P>
The president made the statement here Saturday, saying
Mozambique still needs a lot of well-trained police, Domingo, a
weekly paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The first police training class is to open on March 15 with
instructors from Spain, Chissano disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique has got funds of over 30 million U.S. Dollars from
several donor countries for the training programs, which mainly
aims to enroll and train new policemen.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the government will continue its
effort in improving the relations between the law implementing
institution and the public. 
</P>
