<HEADLINE> 24 People Killed in Sectarian Violence in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 11 (Xinhua) -- In an apparent another
sectarian violence, about 24 Shiite Muslims including women and
children were killed and 30 others injured by unidentified gunmen
Sunday morning near Lahore, a major city in eastern Pakistan,
local reports said.
</P>
<P>
According to initial reports, these people were killed at a
religious gathering at Mominpura graveyard near Lahore when four
unidentified gunmen opened indiscriminate firing at them.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen have managed to escape from the spot and no
individual or group has claimed responsibility for the killing so
far, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
About 300 people were killed last year in the rampant sectarian
violence in the Punjab province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
