<HEADLINE> Velappan Offered No. 2 Post in FIFA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-general of the
Asian Football Confederation (AFC) Peter Velappan was quoted
Sunday as saying two top contenders for the FIFA presidency have
offered him the No. 2 post if they win.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Times quoted Velappen as saying, "I have been
offered the post of FIFA general secretary by Lennart Johansson,
as well as by current FIFA general secretary Sepp Blatter, if
either of them is elected to the FIFA presidency."
</P>
<P>
Velappan, a 62-year-old Malaysian, has been the
secretary-general of the AFC since 1978. He will officiate at the
June-July World Cup's two premier venues of Paris and nearby
Saint-Denis.
</P>
<P>
At present, Johansson, the 67-year-old UEFA president, is the
only official who openly announced his candidacy as Joao
Havelange, 82, is to step down after 24 years as president of
FIFA, soccer's governing body, when the World Cup in France
concludes in mid-July.
</P>
<P>
Blatter's contract as general-secretary of FIFA expires in
December. He declined to comment whether he would contend for the
presidency at last week's Football Expo 98 in Sigapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
