<HEADLINE> Museveni Off to Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni is now in Kigali, capital of Rwandan and he will have
talks with Rwandan President Salfina Bizimungu today.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports did not reveal the subjects of their
discussions but estimated that the two sides will focus on the
situation in the Great Lakes region and border issues between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
There are some former government soldiers of Rwanda who
harassed border residents in both countries along their common
border.
</P>
<P>
The recent reports about massacre in northern Rwanda by Hutu
rebels returning from Democratic Congo also attracted attention
from the international community.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day working visit, Museveni was accompanied by
his wife Janet and Eriya Kategaya, the first Deputy Prime
Minister and the Foreign Minister.
</P>
<P>
He was met by Rwandan President Bizimungu and Prime Minister
Cilestine Rugyema at Katuna border post when he stepped on the
land of Uganda's southwestern neighbor of Rwanda Saturday.
</P>
