<HEADLINE> Kampala-Entebbe Highway Cut Off by Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Kampala-Entebbe highway has
been cut off by floods since Saturday, The New Vision paper
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Heavy downpour from early morning Saturday submerged the
highway at Nakasuba, some five kilometers north of Kampala. Most
of the buildings near Namasuba zone were in the water.
</P>
<P>
John Nasasira, the Minister of Works and Transport, was on the
spot to assess the situation. The work to re-open the road will
started tomorrow, he told the paper.
</P>
<P>
The only international airport in Uganda is situated in
Entebbe, a city southwest of the capital Kampala. 
</P>
