<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Private Sector Urged to Develop Solar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Minister for Energy
and Mineral Resources Muhammad Noor Uddin Khan has called upon the
private entrepreneurs to help promote the use of solar energy in
the country to ease the pressure on natural gas, local newspaper
Independent Daily reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a workshop on solar technology in Dhaka Saturday,
the minister said the government would extend all-out cooperation
if any private company came forward to promote solar technology in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Dhaka city is now experiencing a heavy gas shortage due to
excessive household consumption, he said, adding that this crisis
could be solved if solar technology was used.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that Dhaka was becoming a mega city with a
population of 10 million and at least 1.5 million burners would be
needed for household use. This would create an unbearable pressure
on natural gas supply, he observed.
</P>
<P>
Solar technology must be developed not only for the economic
reasons but also for making the environment pollution-free, the
minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
Though Bangladesh is rich in natural gas reserves, but the
present gas production cannot meet the ever-increasing demand.
</P>
</TEXT>
