<HEADLINE> Williams To Replay U.S. Open Opponent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- American Venus Williams is set
to replay last year's US Open final against world number one
Martina Hingis after she defeated Ruxandra Dragomir in the first
round of the Sydney international tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Williams won the first set 6-4 before Romania's Dragomir was
forced to retire with a hamstring injury, giving the American the
chance to make up for the demolition she suffered at the hands of
Swiss teenager Hingis at the US Open last September.
</P>
<P>
Hingis had a bye in the first round. She beat Williams 6-0, 6-4
in just 62 minutes at the US Open final, making the youngest Grand
Slam final pairing of 17-year-old.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Hingis won her first WTA Tour title in Sydney and
then went on to take the Australian Open title in Melbourne two
weeks later. Those two victories helped her take over the top
ranking spot from German Steffi Graf.
</P>
<P>
"I did very well here last year, winning my first title and I'm
looking forward to the beginning of the tournament," Hingis said.
</P>
<P>
In other women's singles first round results on Sunday,
Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria triumphed over Sabine Appelmans of
Belgium 6-1, 1-6, 6-3 and Austria's Barbara Paulus waltzed past
Miriam Oremans of the Netherlands 6-0, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
