<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Third Private Airlines Begins Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's third private
airlines, Air Parabat, Sunday launched short take-off and landing
services on three domestic routes, local press report on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Maiden flight of the airlines took off Sunday morning from
the Dhaka's old Tejgaon Airport on a 45-minute flight to Sylhet
town 208 kilometers northeast of here.
</P>
<P>
At the initial stage, Air Parabat will operate on three routes
linking Dhaka with Sylhet, Jessore and Bajshahi.
</P>
<P>
Another two flights will also operate on Dhaka-Chittagong and
Dhaka-Barisal routes from next week.
</P>
<P>
Subsequently, the airlines will extend its services to five
other cities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Air Parabat initially maintains its operation with two 19-seat
Czech-made aircraft, and will procure more planes in the future.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi government encourages private sectors to run
airlines to meet growing domestic demand. At present, there are
three private airlines altogether, the other two airlines are Air
Aerobengal and Air Barabat.  
</P>
</TEXT>
