<HEADLINE> Bulgaria, Russia Have Differences Over Gas Supply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria and Russia still have
differences on the supply of Russian natural gas to Bulgaria,
Kiril Gegov, deputy chief of the Bulgarian Energy Committee, said
here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Gegov, who had just returned from Moscow after a three-day
visit, said during his stay there the two sides also discussed the
issues of transit of Russian gas through his country and the
expansion of the transiting facilities.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to continue working on the transit rates of Russian
gas through Bulgaria because there are differences in their
proposed methods for calculation.
</P>
<P>
However, Gegov stressed that nothing threatens the supply of
Russian natural gas to Bulgaria and the gas transits to the Balkan
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
