<HEADLINE> Team Canada to Leave for Mexico Without Chretien </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien said Saturday that the Team Canada Trade Mission will leave
for Mexico and South America without him.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Canada's Governor General Romeo LeBlanc will take the
place of Chretien, who would stay at home dealing with the ravaging
ice storms in eastern Ontario and Quebec provinces.
</P>
<P>
"I am disappointed that I will not be able to leave with the Team
Canada mission tomorrow because of the unprecedented ice storm crisis
in Canada," Chretien said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The mission to Mexico, Brazil, Argentina and Chile will bring
hundreds of entrepreneurs to these countries to discuss trade and
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to joining the trade mission as quickly as events
permit," said Chretien, who inspected the hardest-hit areas in Ontario
and Quebec Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The premiers of Canada's two largest provinces will also stay home
until the situation is under control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
