<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Toll Rises in North China Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHANGBEI (Hebei), January 11 (Xinhua) -- Forty-seven people
have died and over 9,000 people have suffered injuries, including
1,246 people with serious injuries, in the earthquake on Saturday
which struck Shangyi and Zhangbei counties in Zhangjiakou
Prefecture, north China's Hebei Province, lastest statistics
showed.
</P>
<P>
The quake measuring 6.2 on the Richter Scale hit the area,
located some 220 kilometers northwest of Beijing, the Chinese
capital, at 11:50 a.m. (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
By 22:00 p.m., at least 11,246 houses had collapsed in
Zhangbei, Shangyi and neighboring Wanquan County, and another
13,400 houses become dangerous houses.
</P>
<P>
The direct economic losses are estimated at least one billion
yuan (120 million US dollars), according to preliminary
estimation.
</P>
<P>
Ge Zhizhou, deputy head of the State Seismological Bureau who
arrived at Zhangbei with a group of quake experts six hours after
the strong quake, believed that the earthquake intensity reached
around 8 degrees.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua that the architectural structure of the houses
have close connections with the collapse of so many houses in the
quake hit areas.
</P>
<P>
He said, in some towns of Zhangbei, most of the collapsed
houses were built with stones. The walls are soft inside while
hard outside, which are easy to be toppled down.
</P>
<P>
The expert also attributed the shallow seismic focus to the
collapse of so many houses.
</P>
<P>
The tremors were felt by people living over a large area,
including Baotou and Hohhot in the west, Qinghuangdao and Tianjin
to the east, and Shijiazhuang and Taiyuan to the south.
</P>
<P>
Three aftershocks measuring 4.6, 4.5 and 4.2 on the Richter
Scale were recorded after 18:00 p.m. (Beijing Time) yesterday,
according to the latest report from the State Seismological Bureau
(SSB).
</P>
<P>
A provincial Party and government work team, led by Xu Yongyao,
deputy secretary of the Hebei Provincial Party Committee, arrived
at the affected area a few hours after the quake to direct relief
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has also allocated relief funds
totalling 500,000 yuan, and medical teams and various relief
supplies have been sent to the area. Medical teams have also
arrived at the area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a group of officers of the provincial military
command also rushed to the affected area to direct rescue work by
some 1,500 soldiers of the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
The Party Central Committee and the State Council are highly
concerned about the well-being of quake victims. President Jiang
Zemin, who is also Party General Secretary, and Premier Li Peng
called on provincial leaders in Hebei to assess damage and exhibit
great concern for the victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
