<HEADLINE> Czech Republic's Jobless Hit Post-War High in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 10 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate of the
Czech Republic hit a post-war record high of 5.2 percent in 1997
and economists say the rate may further grow, reports said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
More than 269,000 Czechs were out of jobs. The rate was the
highest since the end of World War II.
</P>
<P>
In some counties in the northwest, unemployment was more than
12 percent. Some 56.4 percent of the total unemployed were women.
</P>
<P>
Economists predict the jobless rate may rise to 6 percent this
year as the country further restructures its economy. In 1996, the
jobless rate was only 3.5 percent. 
</P>
