<HEADLINE> Castro Highlights Collective Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro
called to improve the collective leadership mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban leader made the remarks in a speech delivered
Saturday morning to leaders of the eastern province of Santiago de
Cuba, who are preparing for the elections to be held on January 11.
</P>
<P>
Castro said that the role of leaders must be substituted by
other concepts and by a system of selection and mechanisms of more
perfect direction.
</P>
<P>
He underscored that despite the fact that the founders of the
Cuban revolutionary process were just a handful of men, there are
now hundreds of thousands of men with extraordinary merits and
millions of them fight a difficult battle, heroic and glorious.
</P>
<P>
"The country and the party will always need men of great
prestige and authority to perform determined functions," He said.
Great efforts were necessary in trying to find those who were the
most qualified.
</P>
<P>
"In the future, the collective experiences will be more
valuable than the individual experiences," he said referring to
the democratic concept of the Cuban electoral system.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the selection mechanisms would be improved gradually
and those of consultation more efficient. 
</P>
