<HEADLINE> Disease Prevention Stressed to Protect Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Thai authorities will put
special emphasis on the prevention of diseases that could hurt the
country's image during its two-year "amazing Thailand" tourism
campaign (1998 to 1999).
</P>
<P>
Efforts were being made to counter health problem that could
affect tourism and worsen the economy, Prakrom Vuthiphong,
permanent secretary for Public Health Ministry was quoted Sunday
by local press as saying.
