<HEADLINE> Santoro Reaches Final in Qatar Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DOHA, January 10 (Xinhua) -- France's Fabrice Santoro reached
the final of the Qatar Open on Saturday by beating big servers
Greg Rusedski and Goran Ivanisevic in the space of a few hours.
</P>
<P>
In the final, the eighth seed Frenchman would meet Petr Korda
who booked his place by overcoming Briton Tim Henman and seventh
seed Andrei Medvedev of the Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
Santoro posted a 6-2, 3-6, 6-3 quarter win over Rusedski, the
top seed and U.S. Open finalist last year before beating
Ivanisevic in straight sets 6-1, 6-4 in just one hour.
</P>
<P>
Rain on Friday forced the organisers to postpone the quarter-
and semifinals into a single day.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski's powerful serve was not in full working order in the
first set and Santoro kept the Canadian-born Briton on the
defensive with double-fisted drives.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski's sloppy volleying and careless groundstrokes lost him
the initiative in the deciding set and Santoro wrapped up the
match.
</P>
<P>
Henman, seeded five and runner-up to Jim Courier here in 1997,
lost to third seed Korda 7-5, 4-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Medvedev defeated Sjeng Schalken of the Netherlands 4-6, 6-4,
6-4 while fourth-seeded Ivanisevic defeated German wild card Bernd
Karbacher 7-6, 6-7, 6-3 in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinal, Korda had few problems downing Medvedev 6-3,
6-4. 
</P>
