<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary's GNP Grows by 4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's gross national
product grew by 4 percent last year, the highest growth since
1990, reports said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian Finance Minister Medgyessy Peter was quoted by the
Nepszava newspaper as saying in his 1997 economic report that the
GNP growth was even higher than a government estimate of 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Medgyessy said the budget deficit was 4.6 percent of the GNP,
less than a predicted 4.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of the country's foreign debt to GNP declined
from 72 percent in 1996 to 64 percent in 1997 and was expected to
further drop below 60 percent within the next couple of years.
</P>
</TEXT>
