<HEADLINE> Pak PM Expresses Sorrow Over Loss of Lives in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif has expressed his deep grief and sorrow over the
human and property losses in an earthquake occurred Saturday in
China.
</P>
<P>
"We equally share the sorrow with our Chinese brethren in this
difficult hour," said Sharif in a message sent to the government
of the People's Republic of China, according to a statement issued
by the Prime Minister's office Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Following a special instruction of Sharif, relief goods are
being sent to China to meet immediate needs of victims of the
earthquake, the statement said,
</P>
<P>
The earthquake measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale hit Shangyi
and Zhangbei counties in Zhangjiakou Prefecture in China's
northern province of Hebei at about 11:50 a.m. Saturday (Beijing
Time).
</P>
<P>
At least 47 people have reportedly died and more than 2,000
were injured in the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 70,000 houses have reportedly collapsed or
been heavily damaged, leaving tens of thousands of people
displaced.  
