<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Afghan Women Refugees Demand for Due Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 10 (Xinhua) -- Afghan women refugees
residing in Quetta, provincial capital of Baluchistan, staged a
protest Saturday, urging the international community to pay
attention to the plight of Afghan women and help them secure their
rights.
</P>
<P>
The protest rally was attended by more than 200 Afghan refugee
women. They criticized both the Northern Alliance and the Taliban
for the denying of their due rights, according to the Associated
Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The speakers, most of them were teachers, said that during the
former Soviet occupation of Afghanistan, Afghan women too offered
sacrifices but now they had been imprisoned in their houses.
</P>
<P>
They demanded that the Afghan women be given the right to
education. They argued that a nation could not prosper by keeping
half of its population in houses.
</P>
<P>
The rally organizers said they did not belong to any faction in
Afghanistan and were making efforts for the women rights on their
own.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
