<DOCNO> XIE19980111.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak Government Committed to Promoting Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 11 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Minister for Labor,
Sports and Tourism Rashid Ahmad said here Saturday the government
was committed to promoting tourism through involvement of the
private sector.
</P>
<P>
The Minister said that the government led by Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif was keen to promote tourism in the country and active
steps were being taken in this regard.
</P>
<P>
"It is impossible to achieve progress and prosperity in the
country without promoting tourism," Ahmad said at a local
reception held by the Hotel, Motel and Restaurant Association of
Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
He said that it was not a job of the government to run hotels
and restaurants and this task should be done by the private
sector.
</P>
<P>
The government wanted the private sector to run the hotels and
motels currently being run under Ministry of tourism, said Ahmad.
</P>
<P>
He asked the Association to come up with their useful
suggestions for the promotion of tourism in Pakistan and added
that the government would make efforts to implement them.
</P>
<P>
He said that Pakistan has great potential for the promotion of
tourism in the country, due to its scenic beauty, lofty and snow
clad mountains in northern areas of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Minister urged the private sector to explore them for their
own benefits and for the economic prosperity of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
