<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rare Disease Kills 5,000 Cattle in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, January 10 (Xinhua) -- A rare disease has killed more
than 5,000 cattle in the province of Manabi, local reports said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The disease, which cattle raisers call "the inflater" was
detected last September. But the cause of the disease has not yet
been determined scientifically.
</P>
<P>
"The only thing we have detected is that there is a bacterium
that reproduces rapidly because of the high humidity in the
grazing lands," said Ignacio Palacios, head of the Provincial
Agriculture and Livestock Direction.
</P>
<P>
The disease could be caused by the high humidity and the high
rate of parasitism in the herds, he added.
</P>
<P>
More deaths are expected as many cattle raisers have not
recognized the need of carrying controls.
</P>
<P>
Manabi is one of the provinces with the highest output of milk
and beef in this Andean country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
