<HEADLINE> Brussels Film Festival to Screen Over 200 Films </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 10 (Xinhua) -- The 25th Brussels
International Film Festival, which is going to be held between
January 20 and 31, will screen more than 200 films from nearly 30
countries.
</P>
<P>
Directors Niel Jordan and Oliver Stone and actors Dennis Hopper
and Morgan Freeman, who are considered stars in the film industry,
will show up at the film festival, sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The four stars and French director Bertrand Tavernier will be
presented with special glass trophies, which are awarded each year
to people selected as having made a lasting contribution to the
film industry.
</P>
<P>
The festival has chosen for this year a selection of films from
Ireland to celebrate 25 years of Irish film making. A total of 44
films either by Irish directors or about the Irish people will be
screened during the festival.
</P>
<P>
The selected Irish films are said to include Michael Collins,
Interview With a Vampire, My Left Foot and the Dead.
</P>
<P>
A special panel for the festival will choose the best European
film, best actor and best actress of the past quarter century,
sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
